title: Untamed Alaska (Photo Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Thomasson-Grant | 1987 |  pdf | 0934738289 | 128 pag | 17.5 MB

Forsome, Mount McKinley rising in the pink alpenglow of dawn symbolizes the Alaskan wilderness; for others, a brown bear raking salmon from an icy river embodies the power of this region. But the essence of the wilderness is also in the down of a tundra swan cygnet and the dew clinging to a willow catkin. From windswept dunes on Nunivak Island to luminous ice caves in Glacier Bay, UNTAMED ALASKA vividly depicts the variety and splendor of this rugged land
